WEBVTT

00:01.960 --> 00:08.570
<i>* MTV *</i>

00:08.770 --> 00:11.540
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:11.740 --> 00:18.810
<i>* *</i>

00:36.970 --> 00:39.840
[fire crackling]

00:40.040 --> 00:47.110
<i>* *</i>

00:58.720 --> 01:01.860
[siren wailing]

01:10.100 --> 01:12.270
<i>- All right, Everett,</i>
<i>if your eyes are closed,</i>

01:12.470 --> 01:15.610
<i>all you need to do</i>
<i>is concentrate on your breath.</i>

01:15.800 --> 01:17.470
[horn honks]

01:17.670 --> 01:20.210
- Sorry.
<i>- You don't have to apologize.</i>

01:20.410 --> 01:23.380
<i>Notice the sound. Let it go.</i>
<i>Come back to your breath.</i>

01:23.580 --> 01:24.680
- Maybe I should take
another Ativan.

01:24.880 --> 01:26.120
I only had one so far.

01:26.320 --> 01:28.020
<i>- Did you run this morning?</i>
- Three miles.

01:28.220 --> 01:29.550
<i>- Yoga?</i>
- 20 minutes.

01:29.750 --> 01:31.390
<i>- Then you're doing</i>
<i>everything right.</i>

01:31.590 --> 01:33.060
- But what if I just took
a 1/4 of a pill?

01:33.260 --> 01:34.820
<i>- Everett, you know</i>
<i>what I'm gonna say.</i>

01:35.020 --> 01:36.230
I know, I know, I know.

01:36.430 --> 01:37.360
I'm supposed to push
through the anxiety.

01:37.560 --> 01:38.430
Tell myself
it's not gonna last,

01:38.630 --> 01:39.630
it's not gonna kill me.

01:39.830 --> 01:40.830
And it's-it's
actually just evidence

01:41.030 --> 01:42.000
of my body working
at peak condition.

01:42.200 --> 01:43.900
But I'm pretty sure
peak condition

01:44.100 --> 01:45.340
doesn't feel like there's
a giant fucking weight

01:45.530 --> 01:47.940
crushing me, so can I please
just take another Ativan?

01:48.140 --> 01:49.670
[alert blares]

01:49.870 --> 01:51.410
<i>- Listen, I'm gonna</i>
<i>have to call you back.</i>

01:51.610 --> 01:53.480
<i>They're evacuating</i>
<i>my building.</i>

01:53.680 --> 01:55.280
<i>You're not anywhere</i>
<i>near this fire, are you?</i>

01:55.480 --> 01:58.780
<i>* *</i>

01:58.980 --> 02:00.550
What is that?

02:00.750 --> 02:02.190
<i>Everett?</i>

02:02.380 --> 02:03.890
<i>Are you still there?</i>
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

02:04.090 --> 02:05.420
What is that?

02:05.620 --> 02:08.620
<i>- Everett,</i>
<i>can you see the fire?</i>

02:08.820 --> 02:11.030
Yeah. I can see it.

02:12.630 --> 02:14.400
Connor...Hey, Connor,
why are we stopped?

02:14.600 --> 02:15.870
Nobody knows.

02:16.060 --> 02:17.970
Look at that shit out there.

02:19.130 --> 02:20.840
If we have to run, I'm screwed.

02:21.040 --> 02:27.980
<i>* *</i>

02:34.620 --> 02:36.320
- Everyone get back
in your seats.

02:36.520 --> 02:37.990
You guys really aren't
supposed to be up

02:38.190 --> 02:39.760
in the middle of the aisle.

02:39.960 --> 02:43.260
- [horn honks]
- Look at that car.

02:43.460 --> 02:44.890
Huh?

02:45.090 --> 02:47.000
Oh. See that car?

02:47.200 --> 02:48.430
There's no one behind the wheel

02:48.630 --> 02:50.300
like the driver
abandoned their car.

02:50.500 --> 02:51.730
Maybe they're coming back.

02:51.930 --> 02:53.800
- Maybe they didn't want
to burn to death in their car.

02:54.000 --> 03:00.740
<i>* *</i>

03:00.940 --> 03:02.140
Wait, look.

03:05.210 --> 03:06.580
I don't think he's coming back.

03:06.780 --> 03:11.320
<i>* *</i>

03:11.520 --> 03:13.920
Oh, um, it's called
psychogenic tremor.

03:14.120 --> 03:15.860
I've got-got anxiety.

03:16.060 --> 03:18.930
- Doesn't everyone?
- Not like me.

03:19.130 --> 03:22.160
[notifications chiming]

03:23.830 --> 03:25.400
It's from the school.

03:26.800 --> 03:29.340
- You lose your phone?
- Oh, I don't have one.

03:29.540 --> 03:31.810
- You don't have a phone?
- What's the text say?

03:32.010 --> 03:33.380
- What, are you, like,
not allowed to have a phone?

03:33.580 --> 03:35.350
- No. I just--I choose not to.
It's a thing.

03:35.540 --> 03:37.750
You wouldn't get it.
What's the text say?

03:40.120 --> 03:41.450
Classes are cancelled.

03:41.650 --> 03:44.190
They're shutting down
all the schools near the fire.

03:44.390 --> 03:46.360
Wait, why wouldn't I get it?

03:46.560 --> 03:48.090
It's personal preference.

03:48.290 --> 03:50.190
I don't have a phone,
no computer, no email.

03:50.390 --> 03:51.760
Everyone's got a thing.

03:51.960 --> 03:53.030
I've got a thing about phones

03:53.230 --> 03:55.670
and you have
a psychotic tremor.

03:55.860 --> 03:57.570
It's psychogenic tremor.

03:57.770 --> 03:58.700
What's the difference?

03:58.900 --> 04:00.800
I'm not psychotic.

04:01.000 --> 04:02.670
You sure about that?

04:02.870 --> 04:04.570
[chuckles weakly]

04:04.770 --> 04:06.710
- They're evacuating
Altadena and Eagle Rock.

04:06.910 --> 04:08.410
[camera shutter clicks]

04:09.210 --> 04:11.180
- I live in Altadena.
- Did you say Eagle Rock?

04:11.380 --> 04:12.680
Atwater Village, too.

04:12.880 --> 04:14.280
- But they're doing that
to be safe, right?

04:14.480 --> 04:15.890
It doesn't mean our houses
are actually burning down.

04:16.080 --> 04:17.320
If they're saying evacuate,

04:17.520 --> 04:19.620
I think they're pretty worried
about shit burning down.

04:20.560 --> 04:23.260
- Hey, Phoebe, can I borrow
your phone for a sec?

04:23.460 --> 04:24.790
I just need to send a message
to my brother.

04:24.990 --> 04:26.260
For real?

04:26.460 --> 04:27.500
You don't talk to me
for over a year

04:27.700 --> 04:29.570
and now you want
to be friends again?

04:29.770 --> 04:31.700
- No, I-I just want
to borrow your phone.

04:31.900 --> 04:33.500
You're unbelievable.

04:34.740 --> 04:36.110
- You need to open the door
right now.

04:36.300 --> 04:37.470
- If I let all of you
run out into the street,

04:37.670 --> 04:39.580
- I could lose my job.
- We could lose our lives.

04:39.780 --> 04:40.910
I kind of think
that's more important

04:41.110 --> 04:42.410
than your shitty
minimum wage job.

04:42.610 --> 04:44.110
- Can you stop recording me,
please?

04:44.310 --> 04:46.080
- Fuck no.
This is evidence for my parents

04:46.280 --> 04:47.920
when they come pull
my dead body out of here.

04:48.120 --> 04:49.420
- I'm trying to do
the right thing.

04:49.620 --> 04:51.350
- So am I
which I why I'm posting this

04:51.550 --> 04:52.460
so people know who killed

04:52.650 --> 04:54.520
a bus full
of high school students.

04:55.660 --> 04:56.730
[all gasp]

04:59.360 --> 05:01.060
What the fuck is your problem?

05:01.260 --> 05:05.400
<i>* *</i>

05:08.370 --> 05:10.540
- What?
- Don't go out there, Austin.

05:10.740 --> 05:12.480
- [sighs]
- Don't go out there.

05:14.980 --> 05:17.710
[indistinct chatter]

05:17.910 --> 05:24.650
<i>* *</i>

05:26.250 --> 05:29.220
[animals calling]

05:42.870 --> 05:45.240
[hooves trampling]

05:50.550 --> 05:52.210
- What is that?
- Move out of the way!

05:52.410 --> 05:54.020
Back up. Back up. Back up!

05:54.220 --> 05:56.650
[cacophony of animal sounds]

05:56.850 --> 05:59.420
[all shouting]

05:59.620 --> 06:01.060
Get out of the way!

06:01.260 --> 06:02.330
Move, guys!

06:02.520 --> 06:05.230
[indistinct shouting]

06:06.130 --> 06:08.030
- Get out!
- Come on!

06:08.230 --> 06:10.930
[screaming]

06:11.130 --> 06:14.170
<i>* *</i>

06:14.370 --> 06:16.010
Go this way!

06:16.200 --> 06:17.640
Just leave everything!

06:18.740 --> 06:25.680
<i>* *</i>

06:28.920 --> 06:30.620
- Here. Here. Come on.
- Oh, thanks.

06:32.890 --> 06:34.890
[people shouting]

06:35.090 --> 06:36.290
[coughs]

06:36.490 --> 06:38.560
[animals shrieking]

06:40.200 --> 06:41.830
- [grunts]
[glass shatters]

06:46.970 --> 06:49.070
- Come on! Back to the bus.
- What?

06:49.270 --> 06:50.640
There's something out--[grunts]

06:50.840 --> 06:53.010
Austin? Austin!

06:53.210 --> 06:54.640
Oh, fuck.

06:54.840 --> 06:56.080
[coughing]

06:56.280 --> 06:57.250
- [animal bellows]
- [groans]

06:57.450 --> 06:59.620
- Holy shit.
- [groans]

07:00.920 --> 07:02.790
[horse neighs]

07:02.980 --> 07:04.450
[gasps]

07:05.490 --> 07:08.320
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

07:08.520 --> 07:13.330
<i>* *</i>

07:13.530 --> 07:15.930
[animal growling]

07:17.830 --> 07:23.470
<i>* *</i>

07:23.670 --> 07:26.310
- [glass fractures]
- [gasps, pants]

07:37.120 --> 07:38.750
- [yelling
[body thuds]

07:41.320 --> 07:43.930
[horn blaring]
[tires squeal]

07:48.130 --> 07:49.530
[crash]

07:50.670 --> 07:53.700
- [panting]
- [grunts]

07:57.570 --> 07:59.110
- Run. Are you stupid?
Run!

07:59.310 --> 08:06.350
<i>* *</i>

08:17.560 --> 08:19.400
[pants, whimpers]

08:19.590 --> 08:26.140
<i>* *</i>

08:26.330 --> 08:27.640
[person shouts]

08:28.840 --> 08:31.640
[panting]

08:36.010 --> 08:37.850
[grunts]

08:40.080 --> 08:47.020
<i>* *</i>

08:57.170 --> 09:00.040
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:00.240 --> 09:07.080
<i>* *</i>

10:00.760 --> 10:03.670
[siren wailing]

10:08.600 --> 10:10.670
[dog growls]

10:10.870 --> 10:11.770
Shit, Diesel.

10:11.970 --> 10:14.080
[Diesel barks]
Seriously?

10:14.280 --> 10:16.050
Every day? Every single day?

10:16.240 --> 10:17.680
[fence rattles]

10:21.420 --> 10:22.920
- There you are.
I've been trying to reach you.

10:23.120 --> 10:24.190
Why can't you carry
a cell phone

10:24.390 --> 10:26.190
like a normal fucking teenager?

10:26.390 --> 10:27.720
- If you want me to be
a normal fucking teenager,

10:27.920 --> 10:29.320
why don't you try not using
the word "fucking"

10:29.520 --> 10:30.830
when talking to your teenager.

10:31.030 --> 10:32.860
- You should have been here
helping with your brother.

10:33.060 --> 10:35.700
[mumbling]

10:35.900 --> 10:38.970
Danny? Danny, look at me.

10:40.070 --> 10:41.400
Look.

10:42.710 --> 10:44.710
[fidget toy clicks]

10:46.340 --> 10:47.910
- It's okay.
- Look, everyone's saying

10:48.110 --> 10:49.210
the shelters
are filling up fast.

10:49.410 --> 10:50.310
And there's no way
I'm paying for a hotel.

10:50.510 --> 10:51.510
I'm going.

10:52.950 --> 10:54.980
Jacket. Wet.

10:58.250 --> 11:00.290
Don't worry. I'm okay.

11:02.060 --> 11:03.090
[toy clicks]

11:03.290 --> 11:06.100
<i>[ominous music]</i>

11:06.290 --> 11:13.340
<i>* *</i>

11:24.010 --> 11:25.580
[groans]

11:44.330 --> 11:47.500
[high-pitched ringing]

11:50.070 --> 11:52.940
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:53.140 --> 11:56.040
[breathing heavily]

11:58.780 --> 12:05.590
<i>* *</i>

12:11.130 --> 12:12.730
[groans]

12:19.630 --> 12:24.470
<i>* *</i>

12:24.670 --> 12:25.780
Con--

12:25.970 --> 12:32.820
<i>* *</i>

12:38.390 --> 12:41.590
- [muffled] Do you know
what kind of animal bit you?

12:41.790 --> 12:44.160
I said do you know what kind
of animal bit you?

12:46.560 --> 12:48.530
A wolf.

12:48.730 --> 12:49.970
It was a wolf.

12:50.170 --> 12:52.630
[horn honking]

12:52.830 --> 12:54.670
Let's go.

12:54.870 --> 12:56.570
Let's go, let's go.

13:02.910 --> 13:05.150
- Where's Danny?
- Shit.

13:05.350 --> 13:06.520
Weren't you watching him?

13:06.710 --> 13:07.980
- Stay here.
I'll take care of this.

13:08.180 --> 13:10.290
- Christ's sake, Blake,
we don't have time for this.

13:16.760 --> 13:18.990
- Where do you think
you're going?

13:19.190 --> 13:21.900
- There.
- Come on. Let's go.

13:22.100 --> 13:23.730
I said let's go.

13:23.930 --> 13:25.330
Look there.

13:26.970 --> 13:29.500
- You have to speak
in complete sentences, Danny.

13:29.700 --> 13:30.910
Now let's go.

13:31.110 --> 13:32.840
No. Look.

13:34.310 --> 13:37.150
<i>[eerie music]</i>

13:37.350 --> 13:44.420
<i>* *</i>

13:50.390 --> 13:53.160
[bushes rustling]

13:54.630 --> 13:55.930
Let's go.

13:56.130 --> 13:58.300
[Diesel barking]
[fence rattles]

14:02.870 --> 14:05.540
[indistinct chatter]

14:11.080 --> 14:13.650
[breathing shallowly]

14:13.850 --> 14:16.320
<i>[ominous music]</i>

14:16.520 --> 14:19.290
[creature breathing heavily]

14:19.490 --> 14:26.530
<i>* *</i>

14:39.810 --> 14:46.650
<i>* *</i>

14:53.860 --> 14:57.060
[grunting]

14:57.260 --> 15:00.000
<i>[eerie music]</i>

15:00.200 --> 15:06.730
<i>* *</i>

15:17.280 --> 15:20.380
- Hey. Nice to see you
a little more lucid, Everett.

15:20.580 --> 15:22.620
Well, we don't have
any burns from the fire

15:22.820 --> 15:26.720
but you do have
a rather nasty bite

15:26.920 --> 15:28.460
from an animal.

15:28.660 --> 15:31.060
It did look quite a bit worse
when he came in, right?

15:31.260 --> 15:33.230
- Maybe it was all the blood
and the wound wasn't that deep.

15:33.430 --> 15:35.930
- Well, you're pretty lucky,
Everett.

15:36.130 --> 15:38.300
There was quite an accident
on the highway.

15:38.500 --> 15:40.240
Sounds like there were
a lot of car crashes

15:40.440 --> 15:42.400
and animals running everywhere.

15:42.600 --> 15:45.410
- The ram...
- Bighorn sheep. Horses too.

15:45.610 --> 15:46.880
A few stables burned down

15:47.080 --> 15:49.010
and sent them all
running to the hills.

15:49.210 --> 15:51.380
Hey, I want you to relax, okay?

15:51.580 --> 15:53.480
The worst is over.

15:54.850 --> 15:56.690
- So what
about your other friends?

15:56.880 --> 15:58.320
Do you know anybody who made it
here to the hospital

15:58.520 --> 16:00.160
from the highway?

16:00.360 --> 16:02.420
Uh, everybody ran.

16:02.620 --> 16:04.390
Th-there was one. Blake.

16:04.590 --> 16:06.860
- He a friend of yours?
- She. And no.

16:07.060 --> 16:08.660
Not-not really.
I mean, most of my friends

16:08.860 --> 16:10.930
- are online.
- Mm. Okay.

16:11.130 --> 16:13.700
Well, don't worry, kiddo.
We called your parents.

16:13.900 --> 16:16.370
- My parents?
They're coming here?

16:16.570 --> 16:18.540
- That's what happens
when we call the parents.

16:19.670 --> 16:20.880
And they're
usually pretty happy

16:21.080 --> 16:23.280
- to know that you're okay.
- No, no. Not my parents.

16:23.480 --> 16:25.410
- I'm sure everything
will be fine.

16:25.610 --> 16:27.780
- [sighs]
- Okay.

16:29.880 --> 16:32.850
[monitor beeping]

16:35.960 --> 16:38.630
[phone ringing]

16:45.200 --> 16:47.900
Hey, the phone's ringing.

16:49.300 --> 16:50.870
The phone?

16:53.740 --> 16:54.940
[grunts]

17:03.050 --> 17:05.020
Um, hello?

17:06.520 --> 17:08.790
<i>Get out of the hospital.</i>

17:08.990 --> 17:11.430
- Who is this?
<i>- Leave the hospital now.</i>

17:11.630 --> 17:14.430
- <i>Grab your things and go.</i>
- What? Why?

17:14.630 --> 17:16.730
<i>It's going to find you.</i>

17:16.930 --> 17:19.370
<i>It's going to keep coming,</i>
<i>Everett.</i>

17:20.540 --> 17:22.600
How do you know my name?

17:22.800 --> 17:25.640
<i>- It can't move as easily</i>
<i>in daylight.</i>

17:25.840 --> 17:28.710
<i>But it will move</i>
<i>and it will come for you.</i>

17:28.910 --> 17:31.480
Why is this happening to me?

17:31.680 --> 17:33.280
<i>You were bitten.</i>

17:33.480 --> 17:36.620
<i>It has to find you</i>
<i>before the next full moon.</i>

17:36.820 --> 17:38.820
What does it want?

17:39.020 --> 17:41.120
<i>To kill you...</i>

17:41.320 --> 17:42.860
<i>before the full moon.</i>

17:43.060 --> 17:44.530
- There he is.
Jesus, Everett,

17:44.730 --> 17:46.960
what were you thinking?
[phone clatters]

17:47.160 --> 17:49.630
[groans, gasps]

17:53.370 --> 17:54.870
Ev!

17:55.070 --> 17:57.510
<i>* *</i>

17:57.710 --> 18:00.840
[cars honking]

18:04.450 --> 18:07.420
Dad, how far is the shelter?

18:07.620 --> 18:10.390
- Two miles.
May as well be 200.

18:10.590 --> 18:12.190
Never gonna get
through this traffic.

18:12.390 --> 18:14.020
Maybe we should get a hotel.

18:14.220 --> 18:16.690
- Can't afford a hotel.
- Okay, a motel.

18:16.890 --> 18:18.790
- We can't afford a camping
tent right now, Blake.

18:18.990 --> 18:21.460
[groaning]

18:22.800 --> 18:25.200
- Danny, here,
take your fidget cube.

18:27.500 --> 18:28.770
Look, I've got some cash.

18:28.970 --> 18:30.110
I can help pay for a motel.

18:30.310 --> 18:32.440
- Could you stop kicking
my goddamn seat, Danny?

18:32.640 --> 18:34.180
- There's a motel
1/2 a mile down Verdugo.

18:34.380 --> 18:36.280
It's $40 a night.

18:36.480 --> 18:37.910
- How exactly would you
know that?

18:39.750 --> 18:41.450
You really want to know?

18:41.650 --> 18:43.090
[sighs] Forget I asked.

18:43.280 --> 18:44.650
- How about
I give you two options,

18:44.850 --> 18:46.720
you tell me
which one you like better.

18:46.920 --> 18:49.890
Option A,
I fucked a guy there one night.

18:50.090 --> 18:51.230
- Do not do this
in front of Danny.

18:51.430 --> 18:54.060
Option B...

18:54.260 --> 18:56.700
I used my fake ID
to get Danny and I a room

18:56.900 --> 18:58.530
when you and mom were fighting
for six hours

18:58.730 --> 19:00.670
and didn't even notice
we were gone.

19:00.870 --> 19:02.570
And still didn't noticed
after she left

19:02.770 --> 19:04.770
and you got drunk.

19:04.970 --> 19:06.240
When we got back
in the morning,

19:06.440 --> 19:07.680
you also didn't notice

19:07.880 --> 19:09.440
because you were passed out
and hungover.

19:09.640 --> 19:12.980
- [sighs] I'll take option A,
thanks.

19:16.180 --> 19:18.150
- How about you just take us
to the motel?

19:24.960 --> 19:26.730
Fuck this.

19:26.930 --> 19:27.930
[horn honks]
[tires screech]

19:28.130 --> 19:30.630
- Hey!
Hey, what are you doing, man?

19:31.570 --> 19:34.400
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

19:34.600 --> 19:41.680
<i>* *</i>

19:42.810 --> 19:45.850
[growling, screaming]

19:50.390 --> 19:52.620
[gasps]

19:52.820 --> 19:54.360
- Everett, I want you to take
a sip of this.

19:54.560 --> 19:55.990
It has electrolytes.

19:56.190 --> 19:57.430
- I'm okay.
I just got lightheaded.

19:57.630 --> 19:58.790
You really should have stayed

19:58.990 --> 20:00.900
and waited
for the emergency responders.

20:01.100 --> 20:02.400
- Come on, Kendra.
Ease up on him.

20:02.600 --> 20:04.870
It's called hyperbole.

20:05.070 --> 20:07.840
If my son can exaggerate
a minor scratch

20:08.040 --> 20:10.970
into a mortal wound, then I get
to embellish a little too.

20:11.170 --> 20:13.910
- It's not a minor scratch.
- Nothing's minor with you.

20:14.110 --> 20:16.080
- Did they even show you?
Did you look at it?

20:16.280 --> 20:18.150
Here. Look.

20:20.520 --> 20:22.220
- Oh, for God's sake,
Everett.

20:22.420 --> 20:23.920
That's not even gonna scar.

20:26.520 --> 20:32.060
<i>* *</i>

20:34.830 --> 20:37.170
- You can't see it.
- I can see it fine.

20:37.370 --> 20:38.800
Ask your father.

20:42.840 --> 20:46.540
- Oh, I don't know, Ev.
Maybe a little scar.

20:46.740 --> 20:47.980
- Wait, there's a girl.
She got bit too.

20:48.180 --> 20:49.040
The same thing's
probably happening to her.

20:49.240 --> 20:50.550
- What girl?
- You met a girl?

20:50.750 --> 20:51.610
No. I mean, like, I know her.

20:51.810 --> 20:52.780
We have a couple classes
together.

20:52.980 --> 20:54.620
Her name's Blake.
We should find her.

20:55.920 --> 20:56.820
- We need to get out of here.
- No, no, no.

20:57.020 --> 20:58.150
- Lie down.
- No, you're right.

20:58.350 --> 20:59.390
You're right.
It's just a scratch. I'm fine.

20:59.590 --> 21:00.720
- No, no, no.
Come on, Ev.

21:00.920 --> 21:02.220
You passed out twice.
They have to monitor you.

21:02.420 --> 21:03.590
- You're not going anywhere.
- No, we need to get

21:03.790 --> 21:05.090
out of here before night,
before it gets too dark.

21:05.290 --> 21:06.300
It already is night.

21:06.490 --> 21:07.460
- They gave you a sedative.
- What?

21:07.660 --> 21:08.960
You've been out a long time.

21:09.160 --> 21:14.800
<i>* *</i>

21:19.410 --> 21:20.880
[lock beeps, clicks]

21:21.080 --> 21:22.710
[sighs] Go.

21:22.910 --> 21:24.580
[siren wails in distance]

21:26.980 --> 21:28.520
[exhales]

21:32.620 --> 21:34.120
<i>- L.A. highway...</i>
- [sighs]

21:34.320 --> 21:35.660
<i>- Between victims in a violent</i>
<i>and deadly scene.</i>

21:35.860 --> 21:36.990
- Want to help me, please?
- Danny, come on.

21:37.190 --> 21:38.560
<i>- We don't have...</i>
- Let's settle, okay?

21:38.760 --> 21:40.090
<i>- The exact numbers,</i>
<i>but our sources have confirmed</i>

21:40.290 --> 21:41.800
<i>there have been</i>
<i>multiple deaths</i>

21:42.000 --> 21:43.330
<i>from animal attacks</i>

21:43.530 --> 21:46.440
<i>apparently as a direct result</i>
<i>of the wildfires.</i>

21:46.630 --> 21:48.400
<i>Authorities are warning</i>
<i>citizens</i>

21:48.600 --> 21:50.670
<i>to be on the lookout</i>
<i>for bears, coyotes,</i>

21:50.870 --> 21:53.010
<i>and other animals</i>
<i>driven out of their dens.</i>

21:53.210 --> 21:55.410
<i>Many of them</i>
<i>are simply scared and injured.</i>

21:55.610 --> 21:57.580
<i>But as we all know,</i>
<i>fear and pain...</i>

21:57.780 --> 21:58.910
Fear and pain.

21:59.110 --> 22:00.180
<i>- Can result in lethal</i>
<i>consequences.</i>

22:00.380 --> 22:01.620
Okay, if we lose the house,

22:01.820 --> 22:03.390
if it all burns down,
where are we supposed to go?

22:03.580 --> 22:05.150
Is there a government program
for that?

22:05.350 --> 22:06.360
Uh, who can I call?

22:06.550 --> 22:07.690
I-I've got two kids here.

22:07.890 --> 22:09.920
I've got a young child
with autism, okay?

22:10.120 --> 22:12.290
What? No I can't hold.

22:12.490 --> 22:14.730
Yeah, thank you too.

22:16.060 --> 22:17.800
Um, okay.

22:18.000 --> 22:19.330
Uh, listen, I-I think

22:19.530 --> 22:21.100
maybe I should take you guys
to your mom's.

22:21.300 --> 22:23.340
Uh, though I'm pretty sure
she won't pick up if I call.

22:23.540 --> 22:25.040
- We're not going to Mom's.
- How about if you call?

22:25.240 --> 22:26.270
She'll pick up if--

22:26.470 --> 22:27.280
if she sees it's you,
she'll pick up.

22:27.480 --> 22:29.080
She's not gonna know it's me.

22:29.280 --> 22:30.710
Oh, right. No phone.

22:32.080 --> 22:34.250
[shivers]

22:36.550 --> 22:38.950
- Stop it.
- Skin.

22:39.150 --> 22:42.760
- Use complete sentences
like we talked about.

22:42.960 --> 22:45.290
I can't respond
unless you help me understand.

22:47.660 --> 22:50.330
- Your skin.
- No.

22:50.530 --> 22:52.770
Don't you think I know
how bad my skin looks?

22:56.340 --> 22:59.210
<i>[tense music]</i>

22:59.410 --> 23:01.110
<i>* *</i>

23:01.310 --> 23:03.240
Danny, stop.

23:03.440 --> 23:04.810
Your skin.

23:05.010 --> 23:11.850
<i>* *</i>

23:35.280 --> 23:36.680
[groans]

23:38.250 --> 23:45.350
<i>* *</i>

23:48.360 --> 23:49.760
[grunts in pain]

23:51.960 --> 23:54.900
[groaning]

23:56.260 --> 24:02.000
<i>* *</i>

24:02.200 --> 24:05.070
[monitor beeping]

24:16.180 --> 24:19.020
<i>[eerie music]</i>

24:19.220 --> 24:26.090
<i>* *</i>

24:31.730 --> 24:34.870
<i>- I can't believe</i>
<i>how tall the flames...</i>

24:35.070 --> 24:36.870
- I gotta run.
- Where the hell are you going?

24:37.070 --> 24:39.470
- I'm coming right back.
- Blake, wait.

24:39.670 --> 24:42.240
<i>- The highway?</i>
<i>What's going on?</i>

24:42.440 --> 24:44.180
I've been a piece of shit.

24:44.380 --> 24:46.110
I know.

24:46.310 --> 24:49.280
Give me a break, please?

24:49.480 --> 24:52.720
Everything's falling apart
and I-I don't know what to do.

24:53.960 --> 24:57.460
I'm just looking
for a little help

24:57.660 --> 25:00.400
so I can take care
of you and Danny, all right?

25:00.590 --> 25:01.760
- I can take care of myself.
- Yeah, I know.

25:01.960 --> 25:05.130
I know. And you can take care
of Danny too.

25:06.530 --> 25:08.370
Better than I ever can.

25:09.440 --> 25:10.910
Please, just help me out.

25:12.070 --> 25:13.470
Okay?

25:15.210 --> 25:16.740
I'll be right back.

25:19.250 --> 25:22.080
<i>[electronic dance music]</i>

25:22.280 --> 25:29.120
<i>* *</i>

25:45.770 --> 25:48.840
<i>[music crescendos]</i>

25:49.040 --> 25:52.010
<i>* *</i>

25:52.210 --> 25:53.520
Whoo!

25:53.710 --> 26:00.790
<i>* *</i>

26:03.220 --> 26:04.760
Show me again!

26:04.960 --> 26:07.530
[cheering]

26:07.730 --> 26:14.770
<i>* *</i>

26:35.620 --> 26:41.830
<i>* *</i>

26:43.060 --> 26:45.970
[phone buzzing]

26:59.850 --> 27:01.950
Did you like my set?

27:02.150 --> 27:04.490
- Yeah, I did.
Especially that last track.

27:04.680 --> 27:06.490
I can't believe you used
an actual 2-2-4

27:06.690 --> 27:09.390
- instead of a plugin.
- How'd you hear that?

27:09.590 --> 27:10.790
I hear a lot of things.

27:10.990 --> 27:12.830
- You some type
of music prodigy or something?

27:13.030 --> 27:16.160
No. I just know what I like.

27:19.270 --> 27:20.230
How old are you, anyway?

27:20.430 --> 27:21.470
Don't worry.

27:21.670 --> 27:24.210
I'm not, like, high school
or anything.

27:24.400 --> 27:25.340
Follow me.

27:25.540 --> 27:32.610
<i>* *</i>

27:34.750 --> 27:40.220
<i>- * Just want to be closer</i>
<i>to you *</i>

27:42.720 --> 27:48.200
<i>* Just want to be closer</i>
<i>to you *</i>

27:50.660 --> 27:56.570
<i>* Just want to be</i>
<i>closer to you *</i>

27:58.770 --> 28:00.440
<i>* Whoa *</i>

28:00.640 --> 28:07.520
<i>* *</i>

28:07.710 --> 28:09.450
<i>* Yeah, it's like whoa *</i>

28:09.650 --> 28:11.750
<i>* *</i>

28:11.950 --> 28:13.760
<i>* So, like, whoa *</i>

28:16.320 --> 28:18.430
<i>* Just popped her kidney</i>
<i>I bought a million options *</i>

28:18.630 --> 28:20.090
<i>* Of the stock and I stopped</i>
<i>doing the green *</i>

28:20.290 --> 28:21.530
<i>* Man, I rock arenas,</i>
<i>bringing the peace *</i>

28:21.730 --> 28:23.030
<i>* I'm bumping that Pac</i>
<i>in the car *</i>

28:23.230 --> 28:24.400
<i>* Pretending I got</i>
<i>all the eyes on me *</i>

28:24.600 --> 28:25.700
<i>* Got a bad baby</i>
<i>and she's independent *</i>

28:25.900 --> 28:26.800
<i>* Too many people</i>
<i>older than me *</i>

28:27.000 --> 28:28.340
<i>* That's seeking attention *</i>

28:28.540 --> 28:29.400
<i>* When they warned me</i>
<i>about the goofies, man *</i>

28:29.600 --> 28:30.400
<i>* I should have listened *</i>

28:30.600 --> 28:33.210
[heartbeat thumping]

28:33.410 --> 28:35.240
[exhales]

28:36.780 --> 28:38.610
[muffled voices]

28:38.810 --> 28:40.980
[cheering]

28:50.290 --> 28:54.800
<i>* *</i>

28:55.000 --> 28:58.130
She a friend of yours?

28:58.330 --> 29:00.470
No. She's my sister.

29:00.670 --> 29:03.540
<i>* *</i>

29:03.740 --> 29:05.470
- He looked nice.
What's his name?

29:05.670 --> 29:06.670
Fuck off.

29:06.870 --> 29:08.110
- Is that his first
or last name?

29:08.310 --> 29:10.780
- Look, he doesn't know
my name either, all right?

29:10.980 --> 29:12.480
- Dad isn't responding
to texts.

29:12.680 --> 29:13.950
So?

29:14.150 --> 29:16.220
- So I think
he might be missing.

29:16.420 --> 29:17.650
He's a park ranger.

29:17.850 --> 29:19.690
They don't go missing
in the middle of the woods.

29:19.890 --> 29:22.460
It doesn't feel right.

29:22.660 --> 29:25.590
- Come on, Luna.
You know what happens.

29:25.790 --> 29:27.400
Sometime tomorrow
he's gonna come

29:27.590 --> 29:28.730
stumbling through
the front door

29:28.930 --> 29:30.430
covered in ash
and fall asleep on the couch.

29:30.630 --> 29:31.730
And then he's gonna wake up

29:31.930 --> 29:32.900
coughing like he's got
pneumonia

29:33.100 --> 29:34.840
and go and do it again.

29:35.040 --> 29:36.400
Look, can you just let it go?

29:36.600 --> 29:37.740
It's Friday night.

29:37.940 --> 29:39.410
This party only happens
once a month.

29:39.610 --> 29:42.110
- He's our father.
- Yeah, but not our real one.

29:42.310 --> 29:45.010
<i>* *</i>

29:45.210 --> 29:48.180
- I didn't say that.
- Yeah, you kind of did.

29:48.380 --> 29:50.380
Look, are you gonna help me
find him or not?

29:50.580 --> 29:52.520
<i>* *</i>

29:52.720 --> 29:55.290
Fine. I'll find him myself.

29:55.490 --> 29:59.160
My sense of smell
is better tonight anyway.

29:59.360 --> 30:01.100
Hey, wait.

30:01.300 --> 30:03.000
Wait!

30:03.200 --> 30:05.900
- How much better?
- A lot. Why?

30:06.100 --> 30:08.340
- My hearing is
turned up to 10.

30:08.540 --> 30:10.300
It's never been this good.

30:10.500 --> 30:12.540
Not even on a full moon.

30:12.740 --> 30:14.380
Same with me.

30:14.570 --> 30:16.740
But the full moon
isn't for another two nights.

30:16.940 --> 30:18.310
- How many times
did you text Dad?

30:18.510 --> 30:19.650
I don't know. A lot.

30:19.850 --> 30:22.150
<i>* *</i>

30:22.350 --> 30:23.720
- If we went out there,
do you think

30:23.920 --> 30:25.450
you'd be able to smell
anything besides smoke?

30:25.650 --> 30:26.590
Yeah, that's why I need you.

30:26.790 --> 30:27.920
I need your hearing.

30:28.120 --> 30:29.060
- You know what a fire that big
sounds like?

30:29.260 --> 30:30.560
Like a jet engine
throttling up.

30:30.760 --> 30:32.990
[phone buzzes]

30:36.700 --> 30:38.470
They found his truck.

30:38.670 --> 30:39.970
But not him?

30:42.000 --> 30:44.840
<i>[tense music]</i>

30:45.040 --> 30:50.480
<i>* *</i>

30:50.680 --> 30:52.050
You the head nurse?

30:52.250 --> 30:53.710
No, but I can try to help.

30:53.910 --> 30:56.350
- Do you actually know anything
or are you gonna waste my time?

30:56.550 --> 30:58.790
- I'm Investigator Ramsey
with the LAFD.

30:58.990 --> 31:00.590
And this blunt instrument
of the LAPD

31:00.790 --> 31:02.190
is Officer Jang.

31:02.390 --> 31:04.930
We're part of a joint taskforce
investigating the wildfires.

31:05.130 --> 31:06.790
We're looking for anyone
who came in recently

31:06.990 --> 31:08.530
that was injured
on the freeway this morning.

31:08.730 --> 31:10.730
Especially the kids
who were on that school bus.

31:10.930 --> 31:12.200
Yeah, we got one of them.

31:12.400 --> 31:15.400
Walked in on his own.
Lang. Everett Lang.

31:17.840 --> 31:19.910
- Why would the police
want to talk to him?

31:20.110 --> 31:21.210
It's not just the police.

31:21.410 --> 31:23.910
It's an investigator
from the fire department.

31:24.110 --> 31:25.580
You know what that means,
right?

31:25.780 --> 31:27.280
Arson.

31:27.480 --> 31:28.780
[breathing heavily]

31:28.980 --> 31:33.290
<i>* *</i>

31:33.490 --> 31:34.620
[dog whines]

31:34.820 --> 31:41.830
<i>* *</i>

31:50.370 --> 31:51.870
Middleton Road.

31:52.070 --> 31:58.010
<i>* *</i>

32:12.430 --> 32:15.300
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:15.500 --> 32:22.370
<i>* *</i>

32:28.540 --> 32:31.450
[breathing heavily]

32:56.700 --> 32:59.570
[Diesel panting]

33:01.310 --> 33:03.840
What?
You're not gonna bark?

33:09.420 --> 33:11.520
Come. Come on.

33:12.990 --> 33:17.560
<i>* *</i>

33:17.760 --> 33:20.430
All this time we could
have been friends, huh?

33:20.630 --> 33:27.470
<i>* *</i>

33:30.570 --> 33:33.510
[fires crackling]

33:39.780 --> 33:46.920
<i>* *</i>

33:53.660 --> 33:56.560
[indistinct chatter]

34:00.930 --> 34:03.770
<i>[tense music]</i>

34:03.970 --> 34:09.110
<i>* *</i>

34:09.310 --> 34:10.840
- How bad is it?
- It's not great.

34:11.040 --> 34:12.010
We think
it might have been caught

34:12.210 --> 34:13.180
in stampede that went

34:13.380 --> 34:14.420
through the freeway
this morning.

34:14.610 --> 34:16.420
Whether your dad
was actually in the truck

34:16.620 --> 34:18.390
is anyone's guess.

34:18.590 --> 34:21.260
Remember, it probably looks
worse than it is.

34:21.460 --> 34:23.960
These animals were scared
and desperate.

34:24.160 --> 34:25.160
Most of them were on fire

34:25.360 --> 34:26.130
when they came
out of the woods.

34:26.330 --> 34:27.400
What kind of animals?

34:27.590 --> 34:29.560
- Bears, big horns,
mountain lions.

34:29.760 --> 34:31.730
What about wolves?

34:31.930 --> 34:34.040
A wolf couldn't have done that.

34:34.230 --> 34:41.280
<i>* *</i>

34:45.950 --> 34:49.020
[breathing heavily]

34:50.050 --> 34:53.150
[fire crackling]

35:12.310 --> 35:15.410
[floorboards creak]

35:27.550 --> 35:30.490
[rustling]

35:40.600 --> 35:41.670
[grunts] Whoa!

35:41.870 --> 35:42.900
- What the fuck
are you doing here?

35:43.100 --> 35:44.510
- Looking for you.
- Why?

35:44.700 --> 35:46.670
- Because we need to talk
and you don't have a phone.

35:46.870 --> 35:48.080
I don't have a phone

35:48.280 --> 35:49.610
'cause I don't need to talk
to people like you.

35:52.750 --> 35:56.250
Oh, shit. Your house.

35:57.380 --> 35:58.920
This is your house, isn't it?

35:59.120 --> 36:01.260
- [sighs]
Well, this was my house.

36:05.590 --> 36:08.530
- There are fires every year.
- Not like this one.

36:08.730 --> 36:10.130
You heard what they said
on the news.

36:10.330 --> 36:12.630
This is the worst fire
in 18 years.

36:12.830 --> 36:14.700
Just like the one
when Garrett found us.

36:17.340 --> 36:20.410
<i>[somber music]</i>

36:20.610 --> 36:27.480
<i>* *</i>

36:32.020 --> 36:34.050
[whimpering]

36:34.250 --> 36:37.760
What if this time
he found someone else?

36:37.960 --> 36:39.690
Our real father.

36:39.890 --> 36:41.700
- [scoffs]
It's what you wanted, right?

36:41.900 --> 36:43.200
Like you don't?

36:43.400 --> 36:44.670
- I don't want someone
who abandoned us

36:44.860 --> 36:46.330
- 18 years ago.
- But you're the one

36:46.530 --> 36:49.200
always saying you don't feel
like you've found your pack.

36:49.400 --> 36:51.370
Like, no one gets us
and that all you've ever wanted

36:51.570 --> 36:54.070
is to find someone like you.

36:54.270 --> 36:55.580
Well, now's your chance, Luna.

36:55.780 --> 36:56.740
If he's come back,

36:56.940 --> 36:58.610
if he's really still alive,

36:58.810 --> 37:00.680
and...

37:02.880 --> 37:04.420
And if he did that...

37:07.250 --> 37:08.990
Then he's coming
for both of us.

37:09.190 --> 37:13.560
<i>* *</i>

37:13.760 --> 37:15.760
[door creaks open]

37:19.500 --> 37:22.140
Sorry you lost everything.

37:22.340 --> 37:23.900
- [door creaks]
- I don't care.

37:24.100 --> 37:26.010
It doesn't mean anything.

37:26.210 --> 37:27.940
- Nothing?
Like, not even one thing?

37:28.140 --> 37:29.340
Nope.

37:29.540 --> 37:32.310
It's my brother
who's gonna care.

37:32.510 --> 37:34.920
- He's, um--
he's got Asperger's, right?

37:35.110 --> 37:36.880
- No one has Asperger's
anymore.

37:37.080 --> 37:40.350
It all falls under ASD,
Autism Spectrum Disorder.

37:40.550 --> 37:41.520
As long as he sticks
to his rituals,

37:41.720 --> 37:43.160
he's actually
pretty high-functioning.

37:43.360 --> 37:45.890
- What rituals?
[house creaks]

37:46.090 --> 37:47.230
Anytime he walks into a room,

37:47.430 --> 37:48.360
if there's a TV,
he has to turn it on

37:48.560 --> 37:49.960
to make sure it works.

37:50.160 --> 37:52.370
And it has to be playing
the news.

37:52.570 --> 37:55.240
- Well, what if it's not?
- He gets anxious.

37:56.540 --> 38:00.210
Then he has a meltdown--
screaming, crying.

38:00.410 --> 38:01.780
Sometimes he hits himself.

38:08.250 --> 38:10.150
- How come you didn't go
to the hospital?

38:10.350 --> 38:11.450
How come you didn't stay?

38:11.650 --> 38:13.650
- Someone called me
and told me to leave.

38:13.850 --> 38:15.820
He said it was gonna try
and kill me again.

38:16.020 --> 38:17.860
And it had to do it
before the next full moon.

38:19.390 --> 38:21.230
- You should definitely go
back to the hospital.

38:21.430 --> 38:22.760
Probably a psychiatric
hospital.

38:22.960 --> 38:24.270
No. I know what I saw.

38:24.460 --> 38:26.170
People died and it wasn't
because of a fire.

38:26.370 --> 38:27.840
Our bus driver was one of them.

38:28.030 --> 38:29.670
- Renata.
- Who?

38:29.870 --> 38:33.310
- Our bus driver.
Her name was Renata.

38:33.510 --> 38:36.240
[sighs, groans]

38:39.250 --> 38:40.750
Look.

38:42.120 --> 38:44.950
- You see that?
- See what?

38:45.150 --> 38:47.990
<i>* *</i>

38:48.190 --> 38:49.620
[grimaces]

38:52.590 --> 38:53.990
Everyone who looks at it
says it's healing

38:54.190 --> 38:56.230
and it probably
won't even scar.

38:56.430 --> 38:58.630
That's not what you see, is it?

39:00.630 --> 39:02.500
- Look.
- I see it.

39:04.100 --> 39:05.910
No, no, no. Not the bite.

39:09.180 --> 39:11.980
Holy shit.

39:12.180 --> 39:13.780
I can see my abs.

39:16.480 --> 39:19.120
[chuckles] Can you see my abs?

39:19.320 --> 39:21.620
Yeah. Congratulations.

39:23.390 --> 39:25.330
- I look like I put on
ten pounds of muscle.

39:25.530 --> 39:26.690
- You want me to take
a progress pic?

39:26.890 --> 39:28.400
- No, no, no.
I mean I look like I put on

39:28.600 --> 39:30.830
ten pounds of muscle
in the last two hours.

39:33.270 --> 39:35.200
Wait, your skin.

39:35.400 --> 39:36.940
Look at your skin.

39:40.710 --> 39:44.450
You used to have
acne scars, right?

39:46.010 --> 39:49.450
- Whatever's going on with you,
I can't help.

39:49.650 --> 39:50.950
I have
my own shit to deal with.

39:51.150 --> 39:53.550
You and me, we're not in this
together, all right?

39:53.750 --> 39:55.760
- I'm-I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have

39:55.960 --> 39:57.790
said it like that.

39:57.990 --> 39:59.030
[sighs]

40:03.700 --> 40:06.170
[growling]

40:06.370 --> 40:08.770
[rustling]

40:15.240 --> 40:18.110
[werewolf snarling]

40:18.310 --> 40:20.010
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:20.210 --> 40:21.680
[both grunt]

40:26.520 --> 40:28.160
[Diesel barks]

40:28.350 --> 40:29.760
Go!

40:29.960 --> 40:31.990
[snarling]

40:32.190 --> 40:33.330
Ahh!

40:33.530 --> 40:35.160
Other way.

40:35.360 --> 40:39.700
<i>* *</i>

40:39.900 --> 40:41.470
[gasps, pants]

40:41.670 --> 40:43.440
[werewolf snarls]
[Diesel whimpers]

40:43.640 --> 40:45.910
[both panting]

40:46.110 --> 40:47.440
[Diesel whines]

40:47.640 --> 40:54.720
<i>* *</i>

40:56.250 --> 40:59.650
[panting]
For fuck's sake, just go!

41:01.590 --> 41:04.320
[werewolf growls, roars]

41:09.560 --> 41:12.500
[fire crackling]

41:17.600 --> 41:19.640
What, you hear something?

41:21.370 --> 41:23.740
Just the fire.

41:23.940 --> 41:25.610
Do you smell something?

41:27.950 --> 41:29.250
It's gonna be okay.

41:29.450 --> 41:32.090
He knows how to survive
a wildfire.

41:32.290 --> 41:34.350
- I'm not worried
about the fire.

41:35.760 --> 41:38.060
[breathing heavily]

41:38.260 --> 41:41.260
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:41.460 --> 41:48.330
<i>* *</i>

41:51.000 --> 41:53.940
[panting]

41:55.840 --> 41:58.410
[flames roaring]

41:58.610 --> 42:05.490
<i>* *</i>

42:20.670 --> 42:23.500
<i>[somber music]</i>

42:23.700 --> 42:30.580
<i>* *</i>

42:34.080 --> 42:35.880
[recorder beeps]

42:36.080 --> 42:37.850
This is Garrett Briggs.

42:38.050 --> 42:40.120
I'm a Los Angeles
park ranger.

42:40.320 --> 42:44.190
This is a message for my kids,
Harlan and Luna.

42:46.730 --> 42:48.530
Hey, guys.

42:48.730 --> 42:50.730
I don't know if I'm gonna
make it out of here.

42:50.930 --> 42:52.570
And if I don't,

42:52.770 --> 42:55.240
I wanted to make sure
there's a message.

42:55.430 --> 42:57.300
<i>You know I love you.</i>

42:57.500 --> 42:59.540
<i>But there's been things...</i>

42:59.740 --> 43:02.110
<i>a lot of things</i>
<i>I haven't said.</i>

43:02.880 --> 43:06.380
Luna, I want you to know
that things are gonna change,

43:06.580 --> 43:07.720
all right?

43:07.910 --> 43:09.250
I know you haven't made
the kind of friends

43:09.450 --> 43:12.150
you were hoping to find
the last few years.

43:12.350 --> 43:15.020
<i>I know how lonely</i>
<i>you feel sometimes.</i>

43:16.690 --> 43:19.890
<i>But I don't want you to worry</i>
<i>about high school.</i>

43:20.090 --> 43:23.130
I promise you,
you'll find your people.

43:25.030 --> 43:26.700
<i>You'll find your pack.</i>

43:28.230 --> 43:33.010
Harlan, look...

43:33.210 --> 43:36.010
I know all we do right now
is argue.

43:37.480 --> 43:40.680
And I'm sorry I couldn't figure
out how to fix that.

43:40.880 --> 43:44.120
<i>Do me a favor and remember</i>
<i>when--when things were good</i>

43:44.320 --> 43:45.720
<i>between us.</i>

43:48.520 --> 43:52.090
Remember all the books
we read together.

43:52.290 --> 43:54.530
Same ones over and over.

43:56.800 --> 43:58.630
Remember that I took you

43:58.830 --> 44:02.040
to every R-rated horror movie
you ever wanted to see

44:02.240 --> 44:04.770
<i>even though</i>
<i>you were only ten...</i>

44:04.970 --> 44:06.140
<i>[chuckles weakly]</i>

44:06.340 --> 44:09.040
And I was the one
who ended up having nightmares.

44:09.240 --> 44:12.780
Remember that I love you...

44:12.980 --> 44:15.580
even though I'm not your--

44:15.780 --> 44:19.750
even though you don't see me
as your real...

44:19.950 --> 44:21.290
[sighs]

44:24.060 --> 44:25.530
Fuck.

44:25.720 --> 44:27.660
[panting]

44:29.030 --> 44:30.660
Come on, Garrett.

44:30.860 --> 44:32.330
Come on.

44:33.670 --> 44:36.540
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

44:36.740 --> 44:39.940
<i>* *</i>

44:40.140 --> 44:42.080
Get up, you asshole.

44:43.780 --> 44:45.580
They need you.

44:47.010 --> 44:48.880
[grunts] They need you.

44:49.080 --> 44:52.120
[breathing heavily]

45:02.200 --> 45:03.760
[splash]

45:05.700 --> 45:11.040
<i>* *</i>

45:11.240 --> 45:13.670
[panting]

45:22.220 --> 45:24.280
- Are you--are you okay, Blake?

45:24.480 --> 45:27.020
- What the fuck was that?
What's happening to us?

45:27.220 --> 45:28.560
What-what's happening to me?

45:28.750 --> 45:30.320
- Just--you just try
to breathe, okay?

45:30.520 --> 45:32.230
- What, like I'm having
a panic attack or something?

45:32.430 --> 45:34.090
- Probably an anxiety attack.
- What's the difference?

45:34.290 --> 45:35.460
- There's a difference,
trust me.

45:35.660 --> 45:37.630
- No, no, no, no.
I don't get anxiety attacks

45:37.830 --> 45:39.870
or panic attacks or whatever
the fuck this is, okay?

45:40.070 --> 45:41.170
I'm just--I'm freaking out.

45:41.370 --> 45:42.540
You know,
sometimes people freak out.

45:42.740 --> 45:44.500
- Yeah. They also have
anxiety attacks.

45:44.700 --> 45:46.070
- [exhales]
- Just try and breathe

45:46.270 --> 45:48.180
in to seven
and then out to 11.

45:48.370 --> 45:49.440
Try shutting the fuck up.

45:49.640 --> 45:50.580
- No, you could try
Lion's Breath.

45:50.780 --> 45:52.080
- What the fuck
is Lion's Breath?

45:52.280 --> 45:53.680
- It's-it's yoga.
It's Simhasana.

45:53.880 --> 45:55.550
It-it can ease anxiety
and reduce panic attacks.

45:55.750 --> 45:58.320
Yoga? You want me to do yoga?

45:58.520 --> 45:59.920
- No. Just the breathing.
Just the breath.

46:00.120 --> 46:01.090
- Try it with me.
- No.

46:01.290 --> 46:02.220
- Try it!
- Fuck you.

46:02.420 --> 46:04.120
- Listen,
you open your eyes wide,

46:04.320 --> 46:05.290
stick your tongue out,

46:05.490 --> 46:06.860
keep saying "Hah"

46:07.060 --> 46:08.260
with as much energy
and force as possible.

46:08.460 --> 46:09.960
- I c--I ca--I can't breathe.

46:10.160 --> 46:11.330
- No, you can do it.
Just do it once.

46:11.530 --> 46:13.700
- I can't breathe.
- You can do it. Just once.

46:13.900 --> 46:15.800
Just once. Okay?

46:16.000 --> 46:17.000
I'll do it with you.

46:17.200 --> 46:18.710
Look at me. Blake.

46:18.910 --> 46:20.070
Eyes wide.

46:20.270 --> 46:21.340
- [inhales]
- Tongue out.

46:21.540 --> 46:24.640
One, two...
both: Hah!

46:24.840 --> 46:27.750
- [exhales]
- Okay. Do it again.

46:27.950 --> 46:28.920
both: Hah!

46:29.120 --> 46:30.350
- [coughs]
- [chuckles]

46:30.550 --> 46:31.820
- Did it work? Even a little?
- [chuckles weakly]

46:32.020 --> 46:33.420
You feel calmer?

46:35.160 --> 46:36.690
I don't know. Maybe.

46:36.890 --> 46:38.560
A little. Yeah.

46:40.630 --> 46:42.030
I should probably teach
my brother how to do that.

46:42.230 --> 46:43.500
[chuckles]

46:45.200 --> 46:46.370
[chuckles softly]

46:46.570 --> 46:49.570
<i>[gentle music]</i>

46:49.770 --> 46:52.670
<i>* *</i>

46:52.870 --> 46:54.040
I have to go.

46:54.240 --> 46:56.280
My father and brother have
no idea where I am.

46:56.480 --> 46:58.480
- Wait, we need
to figure this out.

46:58.680 --> 47:00.180
You think that thing
just showing up at your house

47:00.380 --> 47:01.650
- was a coincidence?
- [scoffs]

47:01.850 --> 47:04.120
- Wherever you go, I guarantee
it shows up there too.

47:04.320 --> 47:05.750
You want to lead it
right to them?

47:05.950 --> 47:08.090
- It was an animal.
- That wasn't an animal.

47:08.290 --> 47:09.620
It was just a stupid animal.

47:09.820 --> 47:12.060
It doesn't know
what motel I'm staying at.

47:12.260 --> 47:13.660
We were bitten.

47:13.860 --> 47:16.130
I know what it was. You do too.

47:16.330 --> 47:17.460
- I don't.
- You do.

47:17.660 --> 47:20.970
- No, I don't.
- Yes. You do.

47:23.170 --> 47:24.070
[grunts]

47:24.270 --> 47:29.340
<i>* *</i>

47:29.540 --> 47:32.580
[phone buzzing]

47:34.350 --> 47:36.450
<i>- Everett,</i>
<i>this is Kristin Ramsey.</i>

47:36.650 --> 47:38.420
<i>I'm in investigator</i>
<i>with the LAFD.</i>

47:40.190 --> 47:41.750
<i>Everett, can you hear me?</i>

47:43.020 --> 47:45.830
[sighs] It's okay.

47:46.030 --> 47:48.630
You don't have to talk to me
if you don't want to.

47:48.830 --> 47:51.660
But I would like you to listen
for a moment.

47:51.860 --> 47:53.870
I know you're shaken up
by what happened today.

47:55.340 --> 47:58.140
<i>You went through something</i>
<i>pretty terrifying.</i>

47:58.340 --> 48:00.510
<i>You saw people die.</i>

48:00.710 --> 48:02.640
But I need your help, Everett.

48:02.840 --> 48:04.310
I need you
to help me figure out

48:04.510 --> 48:05.780
who's responsible
for the deaths

48:05.980 --> 48:07.880
of several people.

48:08.080 --> 48:09.350
That includes
some of your friends

48:09.550 --> 48:11.280
who were on that school bus.

48:14.150 --> 48:16.860
<i>You're gonna hear</i>
<i>that the police suspect arson.</i>

48:17.060 --> 48:18.790
<i>But that's only part</i>
<i>of the truth.</i>

48:20.130 --> 48:23.100
<i>Because it's</i>
<i>not just a suspicion.</i>

48:23.300 --> 48:26.030
<i>I know for certain</i>
<i>this fire was caused by arson.</i>

48:27.800 --> 48:30.900
I can tell you I'm certain
of one other thing.

48:31.100 --> 48:33.510
The arsonist is a teenager.

48:33.710 --> 48:36.610
Might even be someone
you go to school with.

48:36.810 --> 48:38.380
<i>In fact, it's quite possible</i>

48:38.580 --> 48:41.410
this teenager was
on that bus with you.

48:41.610 --> 48:46.520
<i>* *</i>

48:46.720 --> 48:48.690
Do you understand that,
Everett?

48:48.890 --> 48:50.820
<i>The arsonist I'm looking for</i>

48:51.020 --> 48:53.130
<i>might have been sitting</i>
<i>right next to you,</i>

48:53.330 --> 48:55.500
watching the fire
from the windows--

48:55.690 --> 48:58.500
watching people burn to death.

48:58.700 --> 49:01.800
A student. Teenager.

49:02.000 --> 49:03.600
Just like you.

49:07.110 --> 49:09.640
- [growling]
- [groans]

49:11.280 --> 49:14.080
[high-pitched tone ringing]

49:14.280 --> 49:16.950
[grunting]

49:20.350 --> 49:23.190
<i>[eerie music]</i>

49:23.390 --> 49:30.460
<i>* *</i>

49:33.570 --> 49:36.400
[howling continues]

49:36.600 --> 49:43.680
<i>* *</i>

49:46.080 --> 49:48.950
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

49:49.150 --> 49:55.990
<i>* *</i>

50:11.440 --> 50:18.580
<i>* *</i>

50:38.760 --> 50:42.000
- Luna?
- Everett?

50:42.200 --> 50:44.140
- They're the twins
from school, Harlan and Luna.

50:44.340 --> 50:45.670
What are you doing out here?

50:45.870 --> 50:47.070
What are <i>you</i> doing out here?

50:52.040 --> 50:54.510
- You seeing this?
- Yeah, I see it.

50:56.180 --> 50:58.650
- Your eyes are glowing.
- So are yours.

51:01.620 --> 51:03.460
This never happens to us.

51:05.060 --> 51:07.530
- What never happens?
- Any of this.

51:08.760 --> 51:10.060
But it's happening now.

51:10.260 --> 51:12.070
- What? What's happening?
- Luna, stop.

51:12.270 --> 51:15.340
- Tell us.
- We don't even know them.

51:15.530 --> 51:17.600
Why is this happening?

51:17.800 --> 51:19.610
Because we're all here.

51:19.810 --> 51:21.910
All together...

51:22.110 --> 51:23.280
under the moon.

51:23.480 --> 51:26.210
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

51:26.410 --> 51:32.920
<i>* *</i>

51:33.120 --> 51:34.620
Something bit you.

51:36.220 --> 51:38.290
- Don't say it.
- You're like us now.

51:38.490 --> 51:39.790
Don't.

51:41.060 --> 51:42.360
Just like us.

51:42.560 --> 51:46.230
<i>* *</i>

51:46.430 --> 51:47.870
Werewolves.

51:48.070 --> 51:54.910
<i>* *</i>

52:20.930 --> 52:21.830
I just wanna know one thing.

52:22.030 --> 52:23.540
Did something bite you?

52:23.740 --> 52:25.410
[phone rings]

52:26.710 --> 52:28.140
<i>You're not safe.</i>

52:28.340 --> 52:29.910
- You saw what he did
to Garrett's truck.

52:30.110 --> 52:30.980
What do you think
he's gonna be like

52:31.180 --> 52:32.580
<i>on the night of a full moon?</i>

52:32.780 --> 52:34.280
- Glad we could catch you
this time.
